1
00:00:00,900 --> 00:00:02,900
♪

2
00:00:02,910 --> 00:00:07,130
<i>(train chugging)</i>

3
00:00:07,140 --> 00:00:10,270
This just got real.

4
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:17,610
<i>(excited chatter)</i>

5
00:00:17,980 --> 00:00:25,120
<i>♪</i>

6
00:00:29,510 --> 00:00:30,500
Listen up, gang.

7
00:00:30,710 --> 00:00:33,110
We're almost there so I've
got a few things to say.

8
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:36,800
First off, who here besides
me thinks this is the best

9
00:00:36,810 --> 00:00:39,760
Equestria Games delegation
in Ponyville history?

10
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:42,160
<i>(cheers)</i>

11
00:00:42,260 --> 00:00:43,690
<i>(grunting roar)</i>

12
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:45,610
And no matter what
your sport is,

13
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:46,980
we've gotta give it our best

14
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:50,290
because we've all got a genuine
shot at Ponyville gold!

15
00:00:50,310 --> 00:00:53,410
<i>(cheers)</i>

16
00:00:53,460 --> 00:00:56,680
With the possible
exception of Bulk Biceps,

17
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:58,270
Fluttershy and me.

18
00:00:58,530 --> 00:01:01,900
I mean, we're good and all, but
we're up against the Wonderbolts

19
00:01:01,910 --> 00:01:05,030
in the aerial relay, so
gold's kind of a stretch.

20
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:06,260
Let's not kid ourselves.

21
00:01:06,470 --> 00:01:08,030
Don't feel bad, Rainbow Dash.

22
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:10,770
We have absolutely no shot
at winning gold, either!

23
00:01:11,210 --> 00:01:13,790
Uh, that's because you're
carrying the flag for Ponyville

24
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:15,060
in the opening ceremony.

25
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,120
There are no winners.

26
00:01:16,510 --> 00:01:19,830
Winners or not, we still have
the chance to be awesome!

27
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:21,180
That's the spirit.

28
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:22,540
You hear that, everypony?

29
00:01:22,870 --> 00:01:26,460
Winners or not, we all still
have the chance to be awesome!

30
00:01:26,650 --> 00:01:30,650
<i>(cheers)</i>

31
00:01:30,660 --> 00:01:32,120
But uh, let's
still try to win

32
00:01:32,130 --> 00:01:33,830
lots and lots of stuff too, OK?

33
00:01:34,550 --> 00:01:39,270
<i>♪ (military snare drum) </i>

34
00:01:43,370 --> 00:01:44,370
<i>Subtitles by YayPonies
http://yayponies.eu
HoH version</i>

35
00:02:16,030 --> 00:02:19,200
♪

36
00:02:19,210 --> 00:02:21,480
<i>(squealing brakes)</i>

37
00:02:25,810 --> 00:02:29,450
<i>(grunts)</i>

38
00:02:29,780 --> 00:02:32,100
Phew! It's all in there, gang.

39
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:34,360
Leave it to Spike,
champion gear carrier,

40
00:02:34,420 --> 00:02:36,180
for all your
gear-carrying needs.

41
00:02:36,350 --> 00:02:38,700
And the Ponyville flag?
You sure?

42
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:39,990
And what about the flagpole?

43
00:02:40,210 --> 00:02:41,450
In with the portable ramp.

44
00:02:41,590 --> 00:02:42,590
<i>Whoa! (crash)</i>

45
00:02:42,890 --> 00:02:44,430
Give it a rest,
Applebloom.

46
00:02:44,670 --> 00:02:46,400
Spike: Aw she's just
nervous, that's all.

47
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:47,580
Perfectly understandable.

48
00:02:47,870 --> 00:02:50,370
Whenever I'm afraid I'll forget
something and I start to panic,

49
00:02:50,660 --> 00:02:52,940
I have a simple
trick: I count to ten,

50
00:02:53,050 --> 00:02:55,360
and by the time I'm done,
I've calmed myself enough

51
00:02:55,370 --> 00:02:57,360
to get the job done
right every time.

52
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:58,630
Easy peasy cider squeezy.

53
00:02:58,640 --> 00:02:59,810
<i>(galloping hooves)</i>

54
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:00,430
<i>Spike: Hey!</i>

55
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:02,450
Put me down!

56
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:03,730
What's going on?

57
00:03:03,810 --> 00:03:08,480
<i>(galloping)</i>

58
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:10,150
<i>(thud)</i>

59
00:03:10,450 --> 00:03:12,200
Spike! Are you
all right?

60
00:03:12,390 --> 00:03:14,770
A thousand pardons, O
Great and Honorable Spike

61
00:03:14,780 --> 00:03:16,170
the Brave and Glorious.

62
00:03:16,650 --> 00:03:18,110
Huh? Who the what now?

63
00:03:18,310 --> 00:03:20,080
Thanks for bringing
Spike to us.

64
00:03:22,330 --> 00:03:23,220
It's OK, Spike.

65
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:25,710
We'll have our hoofponies
go back for your bags.

66
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:29,410
Can they hang back a sec and
tell me what's going on first?

67
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:32,970
<i>(munch)</i>

68
00:03:33,140 --> 00:03:33,620
<i>(gulp)</i>

69
00:03:33,790 --> 00:03:35,280
Mm mm!

70
00:03:35,540 --> 00:03:38,610
So the ponies here think
I'm some kind of hero, huh?

71
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,080
More of the green ones, please.

72
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,410
I like the green ones.

73
00:03:43,090 --> 00:03:44,240
<i>Twilight: Last time</i>
<i>you were here,</i>

74
00:03:44,450 --> 00:03:46,290
you got the Crystal Heart
to Princess Cadance

75
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:49,260
in time to save this entire
empire from destruction.

76
00:03:49,390 --> 00:03:51,520
You are known
throughout my empire

77
00:03:51,870 --> 00:03:55,760
as Great and Honorable
Spike the Brave and Glorious.

78
00:03:56,150 --> 00:03:57,100
Isn't that awesome?

79
00:03:57,410 --> 00:03:59,070
You're a big shot here, Spike.

80
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:00,940
See that?

81
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,100
<i>That's you!</i>

82
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:04,970
Hello, gorgeous.

83
00:04:05,420 --> 00:04:07,890
This is why we all hope
you'd do us the honor

84
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:10,400
of lighting the torch at
the opening ceremony.

85
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:12,500
You'd be the very
first dragon

86
00:04:12,510 --> 00:04:15,600
in the history of the
Equestria Games to do so.

87
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:17,290
Of course, I'll do it!

88
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:19,870
And bonus: I can do it
with my fire breath.

89
00:04:20,020 --> 00:04:21,430
<i>(whoosh)</i>

90
00:04:23,090 --> 00:04:24,960
<i>(giggle)</i>

91
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:27,900
<i>(roaring crowd)</i>

92
00:04:27,910 --> 00:04:32,070
<i>♪ (ceremonial theme) </i>

93
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:34,390
Places for the
procession, everypony.

94
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:35,720
Two minutes!

95
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:45,640
♪

96
00:04:45,650 --> 00:04:47,880
<i>(crowd cheers)</i>

97
00:04:47,890 --> 00:04:55,020
♪

98
00:05:00,370 --> 00:05:03,460
<i>(giggling)</i>

99
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:05,440
(upper class British accent)
And you're quite certain

100
00:05:05,450 --> 00:05:08,360
you also understand exactly what
you're supposed to do?

101
00:05:08,670 --> 00:05:11,110
I stand where you tell me
until you give me the signal.

102
00:05:11,260 --> 00:05:12,990
And then I walk over
and light the torch.

103
00:05:13,410 --> 00:05:15,250
Mm. Couldn't be simpler.

104
00:05:18,450 --> 00:05:25,590
<i>(roaring cheer)</i>

105
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:28,480
<i>(frightened whimper)</i>

106
00:05:29,470 --> 00:05:33,240
Mr. The Dragon? Are you coming?

107
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,210
Honestly.

108
00:05:35,490 --> 00:05:38,360
Would somepony help him walk?

109
00:05:43,530 --> 00:05:49,050
Now please welcome the
delegation from Ponyville!

110
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:52,110
Ponyville forever! YAY!

111
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:53,610
Awesome!

112
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:54,480
yay

113
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,070
Yeah!

114
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:56,940
<i>(herp)</i>

115
00:05:57,280 --> 00:05:59,980
<i>(cheers)</i>

116
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:00,910
Whoo hoo!

117
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:12,670
<i>♪ (trumpet fanfare) </i>

118
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,620
<i>(stomp stomp)</i>

119
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:17,400
♪

120
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:19,130
This is the signal.

121
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,470
<i>(stomp stomp)</i>

122
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:25,240
I'm giving you the signal now.

123
00:06:26,910 --> 00:06:28,520
Mr. The Dragon!

124
00:06:36,030 --> 00:06:37,470
<i>(big inhale)</i>

125
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:40,090
<i>(cough)</i>

126
00:06:40,490 --> 00:06:41,400
Come on, Spike.

127
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:42,540
Calm yourself.

128
00:06:42,980 --> 00:06:43,650
Count to ten.

129
00:06:44,050 --> 00:06:48,810
One, two, three, thousand,
fourteen thousand,

130
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:51,470
twenty thousand,
thirty thousand!

131
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,110
What's wrong?

132
00:06:57,910 --> 00:06:59,040
<i>(squeak)</i>

133
00:07:00,010 --> 00:07:01,360
Tell me this isn't happening.

134
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:08,130
<i>(chattering)</i>

135
00:07:08,610 --> 00:07:10,690
Equestria, we
have a problem.

136
00:07:14,230 --> 00:07:19,570
♪

137
00:07:19,790 --> 00:07:20,930
<i>(cough)</i>

138
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:24,660
Mr. The Dragon, would you
light the torch already?

139
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:27,770
I don't know what it is, but I
just don't have the stuff today.

140
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,100
Did you bring a match?

141
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:32,050
You're a fire-breathing dragon.

142
00:07:32,290 --> 00:07:32,980
<i>(cough)</i>

143
00:07:33,150 --> 00:07:34,980
Then some cough drops, maybe?

144
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:37,460
Never mind.

145
00:07:37,850 --> 00:07:38,640
I'll keep trying.

146
00:07:40,050 --> 00:07:40,720
<i>(thud)</i>

147
00:07:42,220 --> 00:07:44,250
Somepony go down and help him!

148
00:07:46,820 --> 00:07:48,500
<i>(click click)</i>

149
00:07:48,950 --> 00:07:49,980
Light! Light!

150
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,780
<i>(grunt)</i>

151
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:58,210
<i>(grunts)</i>

152
00:07:58,840 --> 00:08:00,500
<i>(whoosh)</i>

153
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:03,040
<i>(roaring cheer)</i>

154
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:07,800
<i>♪ (trumpet fanfare) </i>

155
00:08:07,850 --> 00:08:08,600
Phew!

156
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:11,250
How did you do that?

157
00:08:11,810 --> 00:08:14,130
I'm...not sure.

158
00:08:14,690 --> 00:08:17,040
Ah well, better
late than never.

159
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:21,750
Let the Games begin!

160
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:22,890
<i>(crowd roars)</i>

161
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:31,010
<i>♪ (trumpet fanfare) </i>

162
00:08:35,340 --> 00:08:37,600
Oh! There are our
little superstars!

163
00:08:38,680 --> 00:08:39,950
You were fabulous!

164
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:42,840
Made me sit up proud like
a cornstalk in August.

165
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:45,010
Ya done good, squirt.

166
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,850
Twilight: You three
really were wonderful.

167
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,460
But does anypony know what
was going on with Spike?

168
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:52,120
He sure seemed to be havin'
a tough time of it out there.

169
00:08:52,420 --> 00:08:54,320
He put things right
in time, though.

170
00:08:54,530 --> 00:08:56,040
Actually, it was me.

171
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:58,140
I didn't want him
to be embarrassed,

172
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,790
so I cast a secret spell
to light it for him.

173
00:09:02,390 --> 00:09:04,380
Oh dear. Have you
told him?

174
00:09:04,620 --> 00:09:07,040
No, but he might have
figured it out on his own.

175
00:09:07,430 --> 00:09:09,210
You gotta tell him just in case.

176
00:09:09,380 --> 00:09:11,990
I know. I'm just afraid
of how he'll take it.

177
00:09:12,180 --> 00:09:14,290
I know what pride he
takes in a job well done.

178
00:09:14,450 --> 00:09:15,820
Psst. Here he
comes now.

179
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:17,470
Act casual.

180
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,250
'Sup.

181
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:23,210
Spike! Is everything OK?

182
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:25,330
I guess. I don't know!

183
00:09:25,820 --> 00:09:27,200
The weirdest thing
happened down there.

184
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,400
Yeah, about that. I--

185
00:09:29,410 --> 00:09:31,570
I mean, there I was,
trying to light the torch,

186
00:09:31,580 --> 00:09:33,110
with all of Equestria watching,

187
00:09:33,390 --> 00:09:35,410
and feeling like the
hugest failure ever.

188
00:09:35,630 --> 00:09:38,280
And then the thing just
lit. It was amazing!

189
00:09:38,610 --> 00:09:41,470
Oh! Phew! I was afraid
you'd be upset.

190
00:09:41,820 --> 00:09:45,130
Upset? Are you kidding? Why
would I be upset to discover

191
00:09:45,140 --> 00:09:48,330
I can light fire with my mind?

192
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:49,780
Huh?

193
00:09:50,170 --> 00:09:51,760
Look! It's the Great
and Honorable Spike

194
00:09:51,770 --> 00:09:52,940
the Brave and Glorious!

195
00:09:53,070 --> 00:09:54,320
Can we get your autograph?

196
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:55,560
Sure!

197
00:09:57,060 --> 00:09:58,940
How you saved our empire
last time you were here

198
00:09:58,950 --> 00:10:00,490
was really amazing.

199
00:10:00,770 --> 00:10:02,920
Aw. You know what
else is amazing?

200
00:10:03,290 --> 00:10:04,440
Watch this!

201
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,230
<i>(distant birds chirping)</i>

202
00:10:08,470 --> 00:10:11,660
<i>(straining grunt)</i>

203
00:10:12,060 --> 00:10:14,600
Don't worry. Once it bursts
into flames through brainpower,

204
00:10:14,610 --> 00:10:16,520
I'll sign another one
for you. Promise.

205
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:20,860
<i>(grunts)</i>

206
00:10:22,370 --> 00:10:24,370
<i>(groan)</i>

207
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:27,100
(softly) Spike, may I have
a word with you a moment?

208
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:31,100
Better be careful with that.
Might burst into flames later.

209
00:10:31,570 --> 00:10:32,420
Delayed reaction.

210
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:35,800
Hey Twi, what is it?

211
00:10:36,310 --> 00:10:38,720
Hold on, hold on!
Give me a second.

212
00:10:39,230 --> 00:10:41,310
If I can set fire to
stuff with my mind,

213
00:10:41,610 --> 00:10:43,710
mindreading must be
just around the corner,

214
00:10:43,940 --> 00:10:46,850
and I predict that you
are about to ask me

215
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:50,580
to set fire to something
with my mind!

216
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:53,570
No. Because you can't.

217
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:56,840
Oh really? So how do you explain
what happened down there

218
00:10:56,850 --> 00:10:58,240
in front of thousands
and thousands--

219
00:10:58,250 --> 00:11:01,520
I did it, Spike. I cast a
spell to do it for you.

220
00:11:01,990 --> 00:11:05,470
... in front of thousands
and thousands...

221
00:11:06,060 --> 00:11:07,300
I'm sorry, Spike.

222
00:11:07,570 --> 00:11:09,820
I just couldn't stand to
see you stuck like that.

223
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,010
You understand, don't you?

224
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:16,410
I, uh...I need to be
alone right now.

225
00:11:17,330 --> 00:11:17,960
Spike?

226
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:25,100
O Great and Honorable Spike
the Brave and Glorious.

227
00:11:25,430 --> 00:11:27,030
Can I get your autograph?

228
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:30,560
Sorry. You should probably
ask somebody special instead.

229
00:11:32,820 --> 00:11:33,950
<i>(cheering)</i>

230
00:11:34,060 --> 00:11:36,630
♪

231
00:11:36,700 --> 00:11:40,440
<i>Our next event:</i>
<i>the aerial relay!</i>

232
00:11:41,190 --> 00:11:42,780
That's Dash and Fluttershy!

233
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:45,530
Oh no, we can't
be late for that!

234
00:11:47,390 --> 00:11:48,880
Miss, step right over here.

235
00:11:50,140 --> 00:11:51,620
<i>Unicorns will no</i>
<i>longer be admitted</i>

236
00:11:51,630 --> 00:11:53,050
<i>without a disabling spell.</i>

237
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:56,730
To prevent cheating.

238
00:11:56,930 --> 00:11:58,770
And make sure you don't
even try casting a spell

239
00:11:58,780 --> 00:11:59,810
<i>or we'll know it.</i>

240
00:12:04,330 --> 00:12:04,930
Hmph!

241
00:12:16,540 --> 00:12:17,110
<i>(clang)</i>

242
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:23,520
If Ponyville medals here
we'll have 8 medals so far,

243
00:12:23,670 --> 00:12:25,750
putting us tied for the
lead with Cloudsdale.

244
00:12:26,890 --> 00:12:28,680
Unless Cloudsdale
medals here, too.

245
00:12:34,050 --> 00:12:34,800
<i>(whoosh)</i>

246
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:38,220
Ms. Harshwhinny, I know
you're really busy but--

247
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,710
What is it?

248
00:12:40,060 --> 00:12:41,810
Maybe there's something else I
can do for the Games, you know,

249
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:45,090
something really worthy of the
Crystal Empire's admiration?

250
00:12:45,450 --> 00:12:47,420
What are you talking about?

251
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:49,570
You lit the torch
for the whole thing!

252
00:12:50,460 --> 00:12:52,880
Well, actually, that
wasn't really--

253
00:12:52,890 --> 00:12:55,120
That wasn't "worthy"
enough for you?

254
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:57,010
For ponies' sake!

255
00:12:57,250 --> 00:13:00,190
Next thing you know, you'll be
asking to put on a rock concert!

256
00:13:00,690 --> 00:13:02,560
Agh! Celebrities.

257
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:04,110
Wait. That's it!

258
00:13:05,780 --> 00:13:06,560
<i>(whoosh)</i>

