now, loud and proud,

271
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:44,130
<i>to the enjoyment of all!</i>

272
00:13:44,220 --> 00:13:47,680
<i>(cheers and applause)</i>

273
00:13:49,150 --> 00:13:54,950
And now, um, the Cloudsdale
anthem, as sung by Spike.

274
00:13:56,260 --> 00:13:58,450
Wait, the Cloudsdale anthem?

275
00:13:58,730 --> 00:14:01,310
They only play the anthem
for the winners, Spike.

276
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,220
The Wonderbolts are
from Cloudsdale!

277
00:14:03,630 --> 00:14:06,460
But I don't know the words
to the Cloudsdale anthem.

278
00:14:06,830 --> 00:14:08,110
I've never even heard it!

279
00:14:11,410 --> 00:14:13,970
<i>Sing for us, O Great</i>
<i>and Honorable Spike</i>

280
00:14:13,980 --> 00:14:15,590
