286
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:29,580
<i>♪ that we like best and</i>
<i>we're proud and we're fast ♪</i>

287
00:14:29,620 --> 00:14:32,730
<i>♪ and we like it because it</i>
<i>really has nice trees ♪</i>

288
00:14:32,860 --> 00:14:35,340
<i>♪ and we love the town</i>
<i>because it's so cool, ♪</i>

289
00:14:35,350 --> 00:14:37,640
<i>♪ and we like to</i>
<i>fly really fast ♪</i>

290
00:14:37,650 --> 00:14:39,320
<i>♪ and everything like that. </i>

291
00:14:39,790 --> 00:14:45,210
<i>♪ Uh, I kind of wish this was</i>
<i>over cause it isn't yet... ♪</i>

292
00:14:45,870 --> 00:14:48,630
<i>♪ over.... Now...oh... </i>

293
00:14:48,740 --> 00:14:49,980
<i>♪ we're the Wonderbolts! </i>

294
00:14:49,990 --> 00:14:51,380
<i>♪ And we're super-fast! </i>

295
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:54,410
<i>♪ And we're clear</i>
<i>from Cloudsdale ♪</i>

296
00:14:54,780 --> 00:14:57,140
<i>♪ We like it there</i>
<i>because it's really nice ♪</i>

297
00:14:57,250 --> 00:14:58,870
<i>♪ and the trees are cool, </i>

298
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:01,020
♪ and I hope this is over now,

299
00:15:01,340 --> 00:15:04,520
<i>♪ and it keeps going on</i>
<i>la la la... ♪</i>

300
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:07,650
♪ and we really love the town

301
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:12,600
<i>♪ So I wish that this</i>
<i>song was over now ♪</i>

302
00:15:13,340 --> 00:15:15,770
<i>♪ Over now... </i>

303
00:15:19,090 --> 00:15:20,990
<i>♪ Over now </i>

304
00:15:23,610 --> 00:15:27,120
<i>(baby crying)</i>

305
00:15:27,350 --> 00:15:28,770
<i>Pinkie Pie from afar:</i>
<i>NAILED IT!</i>

306
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:35,090
Spike, you coming?

307
00:15:35,740 --> 00:15:38,210
Nah, I got this
stuff to pack up.

308
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:41,700
But you've been moping in here
for almost the entire Games.

309
00:15:41,940 --> 00:15:43,790
And tonight's the
closing ceremony.

310
00:15:44,460 --> 00:15:48,360
Which means we leave tomorrow.
Ergo the packing.

311
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:01,440
And so the Games conclude
as they always do

312
00:16:01,780 --> 00:16:04,320
with the Ice Archery finals.

313
00:16:05,090 --> 00:16:08,320
<i>Ice archers, take your places!</i>

314
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,310
<i>(cheers)</i>

315
00:16:10,490 --> 00:16:13,190
Too bad Ponyville doesn't have
any ice archers competing.

316
00:16:13,460 --> 00:16:15,040
We don't have
anyone to root for.

317
00:16:15,290 --> 00:16:15,870
It's OK.

318
00:16:16,030 --> 00:16:18,860
Ponyville has 37 medals
and Cloudsdale 36,

319
00:16:19,050 --> 00:16:21,750
so looks like we'll be medal
champs of the Games anyway!

320
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:22,670
Whoo hoo!

321
00:16:22,790 --> 00:16:25,290
But Cloudsdale has two
ice archery finalists

322
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:26,490
down there right now.

323
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:30,160
<i>If they both place, Cloudsdale</i>
<i>wins the medal count.</i>

324
00:16:30,580 --> 00:16:33,120
So you're saying it all
comes down to this one event?

325
00:16:33,540 --> 00:16:34,380
Pretty much.

326
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:36,790
<i>Oh my gosh! Oh my gosh!</i>
<i>Oh my gosh! Oh my gosh!</i>

327
00:16:38,810 --> 00:16:40,910
Twilight! Come take this
extra seat next to me

328
00:16:40,920 --> 00:16:42,620
and freak out over
the medal count.

329
00:16:42,830 --> 00:16:43,710
I'll show you how.

330
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,810
Oh my gosh! Oh my gosh!
Oh my gosh! Oh my gosh!

331
00:16:46,270 --> 00:16:47,800
Actually I was
looking for Spike.

332
00:16:48,030 --> 00:16:48,800
Have you seen him?

333
00:16:48,980 --> 00:16:49,960
He wouldn't come.

334
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:51,580
We tried to talk him into it.

335
00:16:51,630 --> 00:16:53,090
But he wouldn't listen.

336
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:54,960
You can have his
extra seat, though.

337
00:16:56,590 --> 00:16:57,930
Uh...Twi?

338
00:17:06,140 --> 00:17:07,860
<i>Twilight: Spike? You here?</i>

339
00:17:07,940 --> 00:17:08,510
<i>(splutter)</i>

340
00:17:08,650 --> 00:17:11,530
Uh, yeah. I'm super busy.

341
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,940
Look at all this
packing left to do.

342
00:17:14,260 --> 00:17:14,990
Crazy, right?

343
00:17:15,380 --> 00:17:17,980
No more hiding out.
You're coming with me.

344
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:19,120
Now.

345
00:17:19,620 --> 00:17:23,790
OK, fine. I'll come. Can
I at least wear these?

346
00:17:24,830 --> 00:17:29,510
♪

347
00:17:29,560 --> 00:17:31,270
Those aren't your
average arrows.

348
00:17:31,610 --> 00:17:33,830
<i>They freeze whatever part</i>
<i>of the target they hit.</i>

349
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:37,730
<i>Whoever encases their entire</i>
<i>target in ice first wins.</i>

350
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:40,980
<i>Keep your eye on</i>
<i>Number 7 from Cloudsdale.</i>

351
00:17:41,110 --> 00:17:42,460
<i>He's the favorite.</i>

352
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:47,710
♪

353
00:17:48,020 --> 00:17:49,960
Honestly Spike, I don't
see why you're being

354
00:17:49,970 --> 00:17:51,100
so hard on yourself.

355
00:17:51,630 --> 00:17:54,030
I let everypony down. Twice!

356
00:17:54,580 --> 00:17:55,880
You never let anypony down

357
00:17:55,890 --> 00:17:57,520
so you have no idea
what that's like.

358
00:17:57,680 --> 00:18:00,250
Are you kidding? I've
totally let ponies down.

359
00:18:00,510 --> 00:18:01,530
That's not the point.

360
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:05,000
The torch got lit; the aerial
relay teams got their medals.

361
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:06,370
No harm no foul.

362
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:09,120
Can we at least watch
from inside there?

363
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:11,920
I'm not sure I'm ready to face
crowds in the stands just yet.

364
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:27,790
<i>(crackling)</i>

365
00:18:28,030 --> 00:18:30,040
<i>(gasps)</i>

366
00:18:30,290 --> 00:18:31,810
<i>(panicked screams)</i>

367
00:18:31,830 --> 00:18:32,450
NO!

368
00:18:38,350 --> 00:18:40,130
Steer it towards the field!

369
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,720
Away from the crowds!

370
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:44,030
Somepony cut the
disabling spell!

371
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:45,400
There isn't time!

372
00:18:48,110 --> 00:18:50,060
Dash! Fluttershy! MOVE!

373
00:18:56,620 --> 00:19:00,950
<i>(crackling and hiss)</i>

374
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:15,850
<i>(roaring cheer)</i>

375
00:19:15,990 --> 00:19:18,620
That was awesome!

376
00:19:20,830 --> 00:19:22,910
I just wanted to
thank you personally

377
00:19:22,970 --> 00:19:25,520
for saving those ponies,
and the Games,

378
00:19:25,610 --> 00:19:28,670
O Great and Honorable Spike
the Brave and Glorious.

379
00:19:28,870 --> 00:19:30,690
You must be very proud.

380
00:19:31,990 --> 00:19:32,800
I guess.

381
00:19:33,020 --> 00:19:34,400
All: You guess?

382
00:19:34,790 --> 00:19:36,940
I just saw what needed
to be done and reacted.

383
00:19:37,350 --> 00:19:39,160
It just so happens
I can breathe fire.

384
00:19:39,360 --> 00:19:41,610
If any of you could do that,
you'd have done the same.

385
00:19:41,980 --> 00:19:43,600
Forgive me for
being blunt, Spike,

386
00:19:43,780 --> 00:19:45,760
but you're not makin'
a lick of sense.

387
00:19:46,740 --> 00:19:47,870
It's just how I feel.

388
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,600
Wait a second. I
think I get it.

389
00:19:50,890 --> 00:19:52,760
You keep saying you
let everypony down.

390
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:54,610
But we all keep
saying you didn't.

391
00:19:54,990 --> 00:19:57,850
You know who was disappointed
in you, Spike? You.

392
00:19:58,550 --> 00:20:00,630
And only you can make
it right with you again.

393
00:20:01,190 --> 00:20:02,490
<i>What would that take, Spike?</i>

394
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:06,290
I don't know. Can
you turn back time?

395
00:20:06,670 --> 00:20:09,770
Cause I'd sure like a do-over
on that opening ceremony.

396
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:11,800
We can't turn back time.

397
00:20:12,140 --> 00:20:15,060
But would you do me
the great honor

398
00:20:15,110 --> 00:20:17,080
<i>of lighting fireworks</i>
<i>in my place</i>

399
00:20:17,130 --> 00:20:18,930
<i>at the closing</i>
<i>ceremonies tonight?</i>

400
00:20:19,460 --> 00:20:20,320
Come on, Spike.

401
00:20:20,540 --> 00:20:22,890
You've saved the
Crystal Empire. Twice.

402
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:25,460
I think you can
light some fireworks.

403
00:20:27,950 --> 00:20:30,340
I guess I have to at
least give it a shot.

404
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:33,620
<i>(happy chatter)</i>

405
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:38,020
<i>(cheering)</i>

406
00:20:38,210 --> 00:20:39,080
We did it!

407
00:20:39,300 --> 00:20:41,060
Ponyville won the medal count!

408
00:20:41,220 --> 00:20:43,030
And only by one medal.

409
00:20:43,290 --> 00:20:46,560
Hmm. Wonder which
medal that was?

410
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:47,690
Bam!

411
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:51,260
How's it feel to have opened
the best Equestria Games

412
00:20:51,270 --> 00:20:52,770
in Ponyville history, Squirt?

413
00:20:53,030 --> 00:20:55,300
Probably as good as it
feels to close them.

414
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:02,400
OK, it's time.

415
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:05,940
<i>Spike: You know,</i>
<i>it's kinda weird;</i>

416
00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:08,470
no matter how many times others
<i>tell you you're great,</i>

417
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:10,570
<i>all the praise in</i>
<i>the world means nothing</i>

418
00:21:10,650 --> 00:21:12,080
<i>if you don't feel it inside.</i>

419
00:21:17,020 --> 00:21:18,890
<i>Sometimes, to feel</i>
<i>good about yourself,</i>

420
00:21:19,220 --> 00:21:20,490
<i>you've got to let</i>
<i>go of the past.</i>

421
00:21:21,110 --> 00:21:23,770
<i>That way, when the time comes</i>
<i>to let your greatness fly,</i>

422
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:27,280
<i>you'll be able to</i>
<i>light up the whole sky.</i>

